-- FACTBOX: Largest U.S. buyouts by int'l companies
-- 
-- Mon Jul 14, 2008 12:07pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/07/14/us-mergers-factbox-idUSN1443723920080714

 

 (Reuters) - The following list ranks the largest acquisitions of 
U.S. companies by international firms, according to Thomson Reuters. 

 InBev NV's $52 billion agreement to buy Anheuser-Busch Cos Inc, which would create the world's largest beer maker, ranks as the 
second-largest, behind the 1999 purchase of AirTouch Communications Inc by 
Vodafone Group Plc. 
BUYER                          TARGET                    PRICE (excludes debt) 
1. Vodafone Group Plc          AirTouch Communications   $60.3 billion 
2. InBev NV                    Anheuser-Busch Cos        $52.2 billion 
3. British Petroleum Co        Amoco Corp                $48.2 billion 
4. Daimler-Benz AG             Chrysler Corp             $40.5 billion 
5. Novartis AG                 Alcon Inc                 $27.7 billion 
6. BP Amoco Plc                Atlantic Richfield        $27.2 billion 
7. Deutsche Telekom AG         VoiceStream Wireless      $24.4 billion 
8. Unilever Plc                Best Foods                $21.1 billion 
9. HSBC Holdings               Household International   $15.3 billion 
10. AstraZeneca Plc            MedImmune Inc             $14.6 billion 
SOURCE: Thomson Reuters
 (Compiling by Jessica Hall)
